This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   The user is developing a WeChat bot campus assistant for Chinese Agricultural University (CAU) called CAUCLAW. Over the session, they requested:
   - Verify and fix `.env` configuration for Docker deployment
   - Rename `CAUclaw` → `CAUCLAW` (all uppercase)
   - Add hardcoded welcome message on first user contact and after `/new`
   - Add dynamic loading indicator during long AI responses
   - Smart message splitting for long replies (max 300 chars, semantic boundaries)
   - Fix various deployment issues (db-migrate failing, work-server password errors)
   - Fix bash-tool bug where `2>&1` caused all `.pi/skills` commands to be permanently blocked
   - Implement caching for slow scraping (faculty bios + news content) — **approved but not yet implemented**
   - All communication in Chinese

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - Bun monorepo (`bun@1.3.8`) with workspaces: `gateway`, `work-server`, `school-server`, `db`
   - Docker Compose multi-service setup with multi-stage Dockerfile
   - WeChat personal account bot via `@wechatbot/wechatbot ^2.1.0`
   - AI agent: Qwen3.5-397B-A17B via OpenAI-compatible API (`https://llmapi.blsc.cn/v1`)
   - Session persistence via JSONL files at `.data/wechatbot/{userId}/sessions/`
   - Python skill scripts in `.pi/skills/` (cau-news-scraper, ciee-faculty-scraper, etc.)
   - Drizzle ORM with PostgreSQL, Better Auth
   - bash-tool path security (user workspace read/write, `.pi/skills` read-only)
   - `splitAndSend` + `buildChunks` for WeChat message chunking
   - `welcomedContacts: Set<string>` in-memory deduplication

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`D:\work\caulaw-cau\.env`** (root)
     - Fixed to only contain Docker Compose PostgreSQL vars + OpenAI keys:
     ```
     POSTGRES_USER=postgres
     POSTGRES_PASSWORD=123456
     POSTGRES_DB=postgres
     OPENAI_API_BASE_URL=https://llmapi.blsc.cn/v1
     OPENAI_API_MODEL=Qwen3.5-397B-A17B
     OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-wRH0nzC6MRKlYdpzIRRKRw
     ```

   - **`D:\work\caulaw-cau\packages\gateway\.env`**
     - Unchanged; contains DATABASE_URL, BETTER_AUTH_SECRET, OPENAI vars for Next.js app

   - **`D:\work\caulaw-cau\Dockerfile`**
     - Fixed migrate stage to avoid bun wrapper exit code issue:
     ```dockerfile
     FROM base AS migrate
     COPY --from=deps /app/node_modules ./node_modules
     COPY --from=deps /app/packages/db/node_modules ./packages/db/node_modules
     COPY packages/db ./packages/db
     WORKDIR /app/packages/db
     ENTRYPOINT []
     CMD ["sh", "-c", "cd packages/db && node_modules/.bin/drizzle-kit migrate; exit 0"]
     ```

   - **`packages/work-server/modules/agent/service.ts`** — most heavily modified file
     - `DEFAULT_SYSTEM` prompt: renamed to CAUCLAW, added URL instruction, added no-self-intro instruction
     - `welcomedContacts = new Set<string>()` added to AgentService class
     - `WELCOME` constant extracted for reuse
     - `/new` handler now sends welcome and marks contact as welcomed
     - First-contact check skipped if raw === "/new" (prevents double welcome)
     - `loadingTimer` (6s timeout → sends "⏳ 正在处理中，请稍候...")
     - `typingTimer` (4s interval → keeps sendTyping alive)
     - `splitAndSend()` replaces direct `bot.reply()`
     - `isListItem()` function detects list paragraphs
     - `buildChunks()` with 3-level priority splitting + list block merging

     Key current state of `handleWechatMessage`:
     ```typescript
     const contactKey = `${userId}:${msg.userId}`;
     const WELCOME = "👋 你好！我是 CAUCLAW，中国农业大学校园智能助手。\n\n我能帮你：\n1. 查询农大新闻与信电学院公告\n2. 查询信电学院教师信息\n3. 查询图书馆座位、食堂菜单、校车班次、校园卡余额\n4. 提交或管理课程作业\n5. 设置提醒";

     if (raw === "/new") {
       this.welcomedContacts.add(contactKey);
       await this.reset(userId);
       await bot.reply(msg, WELCOME);
       return;
     }

     if (!this.welcomedContacts.has(contactKey)) {
       this.welcomedContacts.add(contactKey);
       await bot.send(msg.userId, WELCOME);
     }
     ```

     Key `buildChunks` function:
     ```typescript
     const SPLIT_MAX = 300;

     function isListItem(para: string): boolean {
       const s = para.trim();
       return /^[\-\*•·]/.test(s) || /^\d+[.。、）)]\s/.test(s) || /^\d[^\S\n]/.test(s);
     }

     function buildChunks(text: string): string[] {
       if (text.length <= SPLIT_MAX) return [text];
       // merge consecutive list items into blocks
       const rawParas = text.split(/\n\n+/).filter((p) => p.trim());
       const blocks: string[] = [];
       let i = 0;
       while (i < rawParas.length) {
         if (isListItem(rawParas[i]!)) {
           let block = rawParas[i]!;
           i++;
           while (i < rawParas.length && isListItem(rawParas[i]!)) {
             block += "\n\n" + rawParas[i];
             i++;
           }
           blocks.push(block);
         } else {
           blocks.push(rawParas[i]!);
           i++;
         }
       }
       // greedy accumulation by block, then line, then sentence
       const result: string[] = [];
       let current = "";
       for (const block of blocks) {
         const joined = current ? `${current}\n\n${block}` : block;
         if (joined.length <= SPLIT_MAX) { current = joined; continue; }
         if (current) { result.push(current); current = ""; }
         if (block.length <= SPLIT_MAX) { current = block; continue; }
         for (const line of block.split("\n")) {
           if (!line.trim()) continue;
           const lj = current ? `${current}\n${line}` : line;
           if (lj.length <= SPLIT_MAX) { current = lj; continue; }
           if (current) { result.push(current); current = ""; }
           if (line.length <= SPLIT_MAX) { current = line; continue; }
           for (const seg of line.split(/(?<=[。！？；…]+)/)) {
             if (!seg.trim()) continue;
             const sj = current ? `${current}${seg}` : seg;
             if (sj.length <= SPLIT_MAX) { current = sj; }
             else { if (current) result.push(current); current = seg; }
           }
         }
       }
       if (current.trim()) result.push(current.trim());
       return result.length ? result : [text];
     }
     ```

   - **`packages/work-server/lib/agent/bash-tool.ts`**
     - Fixed `2>&1` false-positive blocking `.pi/skills`:
     ```typescript
     const commandForWriteCheck = command.replace(/\d+>&\d+/g, "");
     const hasOutputRedirect = />{1,2}/.test(commandForWriteCheck);
     ```

   - **`packages/work-server/.pi/skills/cau-news-scraper/main.py`** — read, not yet modified
     - Python scraper for CAU news; `run()` fetches list then optionally full content
     - Slow due to per-article HTTP requests with `--fetch-content`

   - **`packages/work-server/.pi/skills/ciee-faculty-scraper/main.py`** — read, not yet modified
     - Python scraper for CIEE faculty; `fetch_bio()` does per-teacher HTTP requests
     - Slow due to network requests to `faculty.cau.edu.cn`

4. Errors and Fixes:
   - **Root `.env` wrong content**: Had gateway vars instead of Postgres vars → Fixed to only have `POSTGRES_USER/PASSWORD/DB`
   - **db-migrate exit code 1**: `bun run migrate` returns 1 even when drizzle-kit succeeds → `ENTRYPOINT []` + `exit 0` in CMD
   - **work-server password auth failure**: Postgres volume initialized with wrong/empty password → `docker compose down -v` to reset
   - **Missing OPENAI keys**: work-server gets env from root `.env` not gateway `.env` → Added OPENAI vars to root `.env`
   - **Docker layer cache**: Changes not picked up → Use `docker compose build --no-cache`
   - **Double welcome message**: Both `welcomedContacts` check and `/new` handler sent welcome → `/new` now adds to Set first, skips first-contact check
   - **AI self-introduction after `/new`**: AI generated its own welcome message → Added system prompt instruction "不要主动自我介绍"
   - **`2>&1` blocking all `.pi/skills` commands**: `hasOutputRedirect` regex matched `>` in `2>&1` → Strip `N>&M` patterns before checking
   - **Chunking split 1️⃣2️⃣ from 3️⃣**: Greedy accumulation hit 300 char limit mid-list → Added `isListItem()` + merge consecutive list items into blocks
   - **URL not clickable in WeChat**: WeChat personal account limitation, no fix available → Accepted as-is

5. Problem Solving:
   - Determined that `bun run migrate` has a wrapper exit code bug with drizzle-kit → bypassed with direct binary call
   - Identified that Docker bun image ENTRYPOINT wraps CMD in `bun run` → reset with `ENTRYPOINT []`
   - Traced persistent `.pi/skills` block to single `2>&1` in one command poisoning all subsequent calls
   - Confirmed library/cafeteria/bus/campus-card/repair skills are real implementations (connect to school-server HTTP API) — kept in welcome message
   - WeChat URL clickability: personal account bots can't send link cards; plain text URLs depend on client recognition

6. All User Messages:
   - "全面学习这个项目，告诉我运行这个项目是步骤是不是docker pull docker compose up -d --build然后再..."
   - "现在将两个.env文件放进去了，检查一下有没有问题（先不需要运行）"
